modules.description: This module enables efficient manipulation of large text buffers through operations like insertion, deletion, and modification at UTF-32 indices, bidirectional conversion between UTF encodings, transactional undo/redo stacks, and customizable iteration over text content or matches. It centers on the `piece_rope` type, which pairs with strings to support persistent edit history and optimized structural transformations. Use cases include text editors requiring robust history management, document processing systems handling multi-encoding text, and applications needing efficient traversal or analysis of large textual datasets.
